iven by the herd. She analyzes the rational vs. nonrational and cognitive vs. emotional forces involved, and she investigates why herding only sometimes works out well. With new perspectives on followers, leaders, and the pros and cons of herd behavior, Baddeley shines vivid light on human behavior in the context of our ever-more-connected world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Social Psychology.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300231823423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300231823.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles